adjectives.description: unabashed (comparative more unabashed, superlative most unabashed)

examples: Synonyms: abashless, composed, poised, unaffected, undaunted, unshamed

entries.meaning: Of actions, emotions, facts, etc.: that are not concealed or disguised, or not eliciting shame.
examples: Synonyms: abashless, barefaced, blatant, impudent, obvious, shameless, unrestrained
